      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs are directly linked to the clinical performance attributes identified in the device risk analysis: construct stiffness, structural yield, and post-yield load capacity.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force defines the onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield energy absorption. All three are explicitly cited in the device risk analysis as critical mechanical performance attributes for pedicle screw systems."
